In the Matter of S. P. BEECHER. No. 12084F. United States Court of Appeals Ninth Circuit. March 5, 1951.

Before DENMAN, Chief Judge, and STEPHENS and ORR, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Beecher has filed a notice of appeal from an order of the district court of December 31, 1947, denying his motion to amend an order of that court of December 12, 1947, appointing Erie W. Horswill, an attorney, to represent Beecher and the estate in certain matters arising out of Beecher’s proceedings under Section 75 of the Bankruptcy Act, 11 U.S.C.A. § 203.

The appeal is dismissed.
